        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-01T14:48:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-01T14:48:00-05:00" n="140"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                <head>140. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Central Intelligence Agency</gloss>
                    to <gloss type="to">Operation <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>
                        Headquarters in Florida</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d140fn1">Source: Central Intelligence Agency,
                        Job 79–01025A, Box 8, Folder 11. Secret; Priority; RYBAT; <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss>. Drafted by [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] on May 1 and approved by
                            <persName corresp="#p_EJD1">J.D. Esterline</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <dateline>
                    <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                        when="1954-05-01T19:48:00+00:00">May 1, 1954, 1948Z</date>.</dateline>
                <p>48933. Ref: A. <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> 230,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d140fn2">Dated January 25. (Ibid., Box 1001, Folder 3)</note> B.
                        <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> 2294.<note n="3" xml:id="d140fn3">Not
                        found.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>In discussion <gloss target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss> tentative thinking
                        pending meeting following <gloss target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss>’s review
                        of <gloss target="#t_LCPANGS1">LCPANGS</gloss> situation with Ambassador is: <list>
                            <label>A.</label>
                            <item>No approach whatever should be made <persName corresp="#p_SGA1"
                                    >Somoza</persName> either by <persName corresp="#p_MFD1"
                                    >Magoffin</persName> or local <gloss target="#t_ODACID1"
                                    >ODACID</gloss> chief as outlined ref A paras 3 and 4. <gloss
                                    target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss> reaffirms ruling against such
                                representations on matters related to <gloss
                                    target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> by its
                                representatives to any foreign government.</item>
                            <label>B.</label>
                            <item>
                                <gloss target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss> concurs re in ref B action
                                which might interpreted to be for info intell purposes only.</item>
                            <label>C.</label>
                            <item>FYI: <gloss target="#t_ODACID1">ODACID</gloss> plans instruct
                                local chiefs <gloss target="#t_KMFLUSH1">KMFLUSH</gloss> and <gloss
                                    target="#t_LCPANGS1">LCPANGS</gloss> to renew efforts pacific
                                settlement present tension in line with <gloss target="#t_ODACID1"
                                    >ODACID</gloss> parallel action in OAS but such efforts will in
                                no way be related to <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                                    >PBSUCCESS</gloss> nor will any reference be made to revelations
                                described in ref B.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Complexities of <gloss target="#t_LCPANGS1">LCPANGS</gloss> situation and
                        best course to follow in observing <gloss target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1"
                            >PBSUCCESS</gloss> needs will be discussed Tuesday. Request at that time
                            <gloss target="#t_LINC1">LINC</gloss> appreciation of possibility [<hi
                            rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>] may be using <gloss
                            target="#t_PBSPBSUCCESS1">PBSUCCESS</gloss> also as cloak for move
                        against <gloss target="#t_LCPANGS1">LCPANGS</gloss>. If we conclude that
                        such possibility exists we shall have to decide what position to take
                        vis-à-vis [<hi rend="italic">name not declassified</hi>].</item>
                </list>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
